-- INTERVIEW-Family Dollar wasting over $300 mln in breakup fees -Icahn 
-- 
-- Tue Aug 19, 2014 09:16AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Aug 19 (Reuters) - Billionaire activist investor Carl Icahn told Reuters late Monday that the Family Dollar <FDO.N> board is wasting more than $300 million in breakup fees to Dollar Tree <DLTR.O> in an attempt to chill a competing bid from Dollar General <DG.N>.

Icahn said: "It appears that (CEO Howard) Levine and Family Dollar wanted to neutralize me by getting me to sign a confidentiality agreement.